Vanilla Custard (Crème Pâtissière)

Ingredients
	•	1¼ cups (300 ml) whole milk
	•	1 vanilla bean (or 2 tsp pure vanilla extract, added off heat)
	•	3 large egg yolks
	•	⅓ cup (60 g) white sugar
	•	3 tbsp (50 g) cornstarch
	•	Pinch fine salt

Method
	1.	Heat milk with split vanilla bean and seeds over medium heat until steaming. Do not boil.
	2.	Whisk yolks, sugar, and salt until pale. Whisk in cornstarch until fully smooth.
	3.	Slowly whisk hot milk into yolk mixture to temper.
	4.	Return to saucepan. Cook over medium heat, whisking constantly, until thick, glossy, and bubbling once.
	5.	Remove from heat. Remove vanilla pod. Optional: pass through fine sieve.
	6.	Press plastic wrap directly onto surface. Chill 40 minutes minimum until cold and pipeable.

Target texture: thick pudding consistency that holds soft peaks.

