Pancake Batter (Light Cake-Style)

Ingredients
	•	1½ cups (180 g) cake flour
	•	2½ tbsp (30 g) white sugar
	•	¼ tsp baking powder
	•	¼ tsp fine salt
	•	2 large eggs
	•	¾ cup + 2 tbsp (200 ml) whole milk
	•	3 tbsp (40 g) unsalted butter, melted and cooled
	•	Neutral oil spray or butter for pan

Method
	1.	Whisk flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt thoroughly.
	2.	In another bowl, whisk eggs, milk, and butter.
	3.	Add wet ingredients to dry. Whisk just until smooth. Do not overmix.
	4.	Rest batter 10 minutes at room temperature.

Target texture: smooth, pourable, ribbons briefly when lifted.

⸻

Cooking & Assembly
	1.	Heat non-stick pan over medium-low. Lightly grease.
	2.	If using rings (recommended): fill rings halfway. Use a spoon to push batter up sides, forming a shallow well.
	3.	Cook slowly until set and lightly golden. Flip carefully.
	4.	Remove rings. Pipe chilled custard into centre.
	5.	Cap with a second pancake. Warm gently 30–60 seconds per side.

⸻

Finishing (Optional, restrained)
	•	Light dusting icing sugar
	•	Fresh berries (raspberry or blueberry preferred)
	•	Warm maple butter: 2 tbsp butter + 1 tbsp Grade A Dark maple syrup